"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-2024-mens-olympic-basketball-qualifying-tournaments-work-explained\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A total of 12 countries will compete for the gold, silver, and bronze medals at the 2024 Olympics Basketball tournament in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998077201057, \"rank\": 1.9228008515302586e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, eight teams have qualified.\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 165, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France qualified as the hosts, and the following seven teams qualified based on their performance at the2023 FIBA World Cup.\\u00c2  Respective gold and silver medalists Germany and Serbia qualified as the top European teams for the World Cup.\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 403, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 166, \"end\": 172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999998814673815, \"rank\": 8.469228968679993e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999033592237011, \"rank\": 9.664809774598984e-05, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 342, \"end\": 348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999826689101829, \"rank\": 0.00017321588398725606, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada and the United States qualified as top performers from the Americas, and Japan, Australia, and South Sudan were the top performers for Asia, Oceania, and Africa respectively.\\u00c2  The final four spots will be determined by the 2024 Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s FIBA Olympic Qualifying Tournaments to be played from July 2-7, about four days after the 2024 NBA Draft.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9989914200930752, \"rank\": 0.0009729693140135319, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 419, \"end\": 432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.231083297741083e-13, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 489, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9863301078032456, \"rank\": 0.013042604435386324, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 500, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999963039017623, \"rank\": 3.6341740703878463e-06, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Oceania\", \"score\": 0.9973053226400015, \"rank\": 0.0026952498882616477, \"text\": \"Oceania\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Oceania\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIBA_Oceania\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"24 teams are participating in this tournament including the 16 non-qualifiers from the 2023 FIBA World Cup, three highest-ranked countries per region in the FIBA world ranking, and five teams who qualified via the Pre-Qualifying tournaments last summer.\\u00c2  The four spots will be determined through four mini-tournaments.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 1074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each of the mini-tournaments will have two groups of three where the top two teams from each group will face each other in the semifinals, with the winners advancing to the final, and the winner of the final will qualify for the 2024 Paris Olympics.\\u00c2  The first tournament will be held in Valencia, Spain, and Lebanon, Angola, and Spain will face off in one group while Finland, Poland, and the Bahamas will face off in the other group.\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valencia_CF\", \"score\": 0.9980167756444316, \"rank\": 0.0014560465290387155, \"text\": \"Valencia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valencia_CF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valencia_CF\"}, {\"begin\": 1374, \"end\": 1379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999811470719613,